      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2002 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black. At its heart is the S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a high-compression head that screams to an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a tactile 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and a variable M-differential lock. The suspension geometry remains precise, providing the communicative steering and neutral handling balance characteristic of the E46 chassis. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including a VANOS system refresh and a thorough subframe reinforcement check. While the aesthetic reflects its status as a well-loved enthusiast machine, the mechanical vitals are robust, ensuring the visceral performance and throttle response expected of a true M-car.",
